description: English compile +‎ -ation, from Middle French, from Latin compilatio (“a raking together, a plundering, a collection of documents”).

entries.meaning: (uncountable) The act or process of compiling or gathering together from various sources.
(countable) That which is compiled; especially, a book or document composed of materials gathering from other books or documents.
examples: Susie made Jasmine a compilation CD of some of best songs they'd heard at the festival.

entries.meaning: (countable, uncountable, computing) Translation of source code into object code by a compiler.
